-Bob. You made it.
-[Bob laughs]

84
00:03:48,394 --> 00:03:49,938
[Kitty coos]

85
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:50,939
‎你知道他要来？
You knew about this?

86
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:53,066
‎你不知道 所以他才来得成
And you didn't, and that's why he's here.

87
00:03:53,149 --> 00:03:54,776
‎-嗨！
‎-嗨
-Hi!
-[Bob] Hi.

88
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:57,820
‎我给你带了新鲜的佛罗里达橙
I brought you some fresh Florida oranges.

89
00:03:57,904 --> 00:03:59,989
‎我在飞机上拿它当枕头来着
I used them as a pillow on the plane.

90
00:04:00,073 --> 00:04:03,701
‎里面要是有卷毛儿 那都是我的
So, if you find any curly hairs in there,
that's me.

91
00:04:04,661 --> 00:04:08,581
‎那我把这些放进洗碗机
Well, I am just gonna put these
in the dishwasher.

92
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:09,707
[both laugh]

93
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:13,002
‎小寿星来啦
There's the birthday girl!

94
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:15,338
‎生日快乐
Happy birthday.

95
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:17,966
‎我先说的
I said it first.

96
00:04:19,008 --> 00:04:20,009
‎嘿 鲍勃姥爷
Hey, Grandpa Bob.

97
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:22,053
‎瞅瞅
Ooh! Look at you.

98
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:25,431
‎你可真漂亮
You are so darn beautiful.

99
00:04:26,015 --> 00:04:29,269
‎潘西亚蒂家的基因依然很牛
Those Pinciotti genes
are strong like a bull.

100
00:04:30,103 --> 00:04:31,229
‎牛啥就不一定了
Bull-something.

101
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,315
‎牛奶是开派对用的！
That milk's for the party!

102
00:04:36,693 --> 00:04:39,279
‎我是说 生日快乐 亲爱的
I mean, happy birthday, honey.

103
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:42,365
‎孩儿啊 生日快乐
Happy birthday, kiddo.

104
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:43,950
‎奶奶没事吧？
Is Grandma all right?

105
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,119
‎最好别惹她
I'd lay low.

106
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,663
[rock music playing]

107
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:53,334
‎如果你连我的名字都不会拼
If you don't even know
how I spell my name,

108
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:55,086
‎那关于我还有什么是你不知道的？
what else do you not know about me?

109
00:04:55,169 --> 00:04:57,380
‎妮可 我也不知道我不知道啥
I don't know what I don't know, Nik.

110
00:04:58,840 --> 00:05:02,427
‎问问我关于你咪咪的事儿
‎我可以画在餐巾纸上
Ask me something about your boobs.
I can draw those on a napkin.

111
00:05:03,761 --> 00:05:05,471
‎你过生日 还请我们吃饭？
You're buying <i>us</i> lunch on <i>your</i> birthday?

112
00:05:06,347 --> 00:05:09,559
‎我觉得应该感谢你们
‎这个礼拜这么照顾我
I felt like I needed to thank you guys
for taking care of me this week.

113
00:05:09,642 --> 00:05:10,810
‎我也没有太惨 是吧？
I wasn't too bad, was I?

114
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:14,897
[laughs heartily, inhales sharply]

115
00:05:15,857 --> 00:05:17,233
‎哦 你没开玩笑啊
Oh, you weren't kidding.

116
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:22,196
‎太好了 你终于意识到
‎在男人身上浪费这么多时间有多傻了
I'm glad you finally realized it's dumb
to let a man waste so much of your time.

117
00:05:22,280 --> 00:05:23,114
‎那是我们该做的
That's our job.

118
00:05:24,365 --> 00:05:26,993
‎你说得对 我要过一个精彩的生日
You're right.
I'm going to have a great birthday.

119
00:05:27,076 --> 00:05:29,245
‎再也不会闷闷不乐了
All that moping around stuff
is in the past.

120
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:30,288
‎很好
Good.

121
00:05:31,080 --> 00:05:32,999
‎因为杰伊和赛琳娜刚刚进来了
'Cause Jay and Serena just walked in.

122
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:35,668
‎糟了 她又要丧了
This is bad. She's gonna have a relapse.

123
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:40,673
‎就是 莉亚 这场面对你没好处 走吧
Yeah. Leia, you don't need this right now.
Let's just get outta here.

124
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:42,383
‎说真的 伙计们 我没事的
Seriously, guys, I'm fine.

125
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:45,053
‎我现在就过去
‎像普通人一样打个招呼
I'm gonna go over there
and say hi like a normal person.

126
00:05:47,347 --> 00:05:48,681
‎你们这些笨蛋怎么样啊？
How's it going, turkeys?

127
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:52,643
‎我喜欢她的肢体语言 坚强 自信
I like her body language.
Strong, assertive.

128
00:05:52,727 --> 00:05:54,228
‎她刚刚拿起一条腌黄瓜
She just picked up a pickle.

129
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:57,440
‎今天是我生日
So today's my birthday. [chuckles]

130
00:05:57,523 --> 00:06:00,109
‎新的一年 全新开始 十五岁可是大年
New year, startin' fresh.
The big one-five.

131
00:06:01,277 --> 00:06:04,697
‎好可爱啊
‎我都不怎么记得十五岁生日了
Aww, that's so cute!
I barely even remember turning 15.

132
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:06,157
‎当时好像是在巴哈马
I think I was in the Bahamas.

133
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:07,658
‎我也是
Me too!

134
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:08,951
‎可你现在在这里啊
But you're here right now.

135
00:06:09,035 --> 00:06:10,411
‎不 在这里的是你
No, you're here.

136
00:06:11,079 --> 00:06:13,122
‎反正呢 今晚开派对
Anywhistle, big party tonight.

137
00:06:13,206 --> 00:06:16,292
‎我奶奶请了桥牌俱乐部的牌友
‎所以肯定是要掀房盖儿了
My grandma's inviting her bridge club,
so the roof shall be raised.

138
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:17,627
[chuckles]

139
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:19,962
‎哎呀 我真没礼貌 你们也来玩吧
Actually, I'm so rude.
You guys should come.

140
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:23,132
‎-你确定吗？
‎-当然了
-Are you sure?
-Of course.

141
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:26,511
‎我希望所有的朋友和他们新女友都来
I want all my friends
and their new girlfriends at my party.

142
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:28,930
‎那太好了 我们去
Okay, great. We'll be there.

143
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:31,933
‎我也是 都等不及了
As will I. Cannot wait.

144
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:36,854
‎我毁了自己的生日
[sighs] I just ruined my birthday.

145
00:06:38,022 --> 00:06:41,109
‎这时候你们该告诉我
‎我没有毁掉自己的生日
This is where you're supposed to tell me
I didn't just ruin my birthday.

146
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:42,151
‎但你有
But you did.

147
00:06:43,236 --> 00:06:44,737
‎这根腌黄瓜真是灾星！
This pickle's bad luck!

148
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:47,073
‎把你的恶魔咸菜拿远点
Don't put your demon pickle near me.

149
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,748
‎你那只手不想要了？
You wanna lose that hand?

150
00:06:56,332 --> 00:07:01,462
‎很少有人能夺走纸杯蛋糕的欢乐
You know, it's hard
to take the joy out of a cupcake.

151
00:07:02,046 --> 00:07:03,047
‎你居然做到了
But you did.

152
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:07,844
‎你要是不想给我帮忙
‎那就去客厅坐着
Well, if you don't wanna help me,
you can go sit in the living room

153
00:07:07,927 --> 00:07:11,180
‎跟鲍勃聊他的假睾丸
and talk to Bob
about his prosthetic testicle.

154
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:14,350
‎你干嘛非请他来？
Why did you have to invite him?

155
00:07:14,434 --> 00:07:18,104
‎我真不懂 你干嘛这么不爽
‎毕竟他是莉亚的外公
I don't know what you're getting
worked up about. He's Leia's grandpa too.

156
00:07:18,187 --> 00:07:19,522
‎都怪艾瑞克
I blame Eric.

157
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:24,527
‎管鲍勃叫爹的姑娘就那么一个
There's only one girl in the world
with Bob as her dad,

158
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:26,988
‎而他偏偏要选她
and he had to pick her.

159
00:07:28,072 --> 00:07:30,032
‎我说 今天有啥菜啊？
Hey there, what's cookin'?

160
00:07:30,700 --> 00:07:32,618
‎在厨房问这个正合适
-'Cause we're in the kitchen.
-Oh.

161
00:07:34,412 --> 00:07:35,538
‎该死
Damn it.

162
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:39,584
‎念叨三回就把他招来了
‎就跟《阴间大法师》似的
We said his name three times
and summoned him like Beetlejuice.

163
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:44,630
‎我来做个拿手的蛤蜊蘸酱
‎为派对助兴
I'm gonna make my famous clam dip
for the party.

164
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:47,842
‎真贴心 但我们已经准备很多吃的了
Oh, that's sweet,
but we have plenty of food for tonight.

165
00:07:47,925 --> 00:07:50,720
‎我知道 但孩子们肯定想吃点好吃的
I know, but the kids are gonna want
something good.

166
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:54,891
‎我在那儿化火腿呢
I was thawing a ham in there.

167
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:58,019
‎我只是太激动了
I'm just excited.

168
00:07:58,102 --> 00:08:02,231
‎莉亚今年过生日 我可是下血本了
You know, I went all out
on Leia's birthday gift this year.

169
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,609
‎我给她买了一台卡拉OK唱机
I got her a karaoke machine.

170
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:08,821
‎-那东西不是很贵吗？
‎-就是啊
-Aren't those things expensive?
-Oh yeah. [chuckles]

171
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:10,531
‎我没撕价签
I left the price tag on.

172
00:08:11,991 --> 00:08:13,910
‎我希望她…能记住我有多爱他
'Cause I want her to…

173
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:15,995
‎我希望她…能记住我有多爱他
[voice breaking]
…remember how much I love her.

174
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:19,207
‎我得静一静
[weeping] I need a minute!

175
00:08:22,084 --> 00:08:24,212
‎这小子以为他能砸我的场子？
This guy thinks he can run my party?

176
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,756
‎拿蛤蜊斗火腿？休想
Clam my ham? No, sir!

177
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:30,510
‎你的火腿好歹还能洗洗干净 凯蒂
You can rinse off your ham, Kitty.

178
00:08:31,052 --> 00:08:34,639
‎我那20块钱刚刚被卡拉OK唱机碾压了
My 20 bucks is getting its ass kicked
by a karaoke machine.

179
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:37,058
‎那就拿出点气势 雷德
Well, then, step it up, Red.

180
00:08:37,141 --> 00:08:39,602
‎你蛋蛋比他多一倍 那就有点种
You've got twice the balls, act like it.

181
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:42,438
[rock music playing]

182
00:08:43,272 --> 00:08:44,690
‎伙计们 我好像想明白
You guys, I think I figured out

183
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:47,068
‎为什么会请杰伊和他女友来派对了
why I invited Jay and his girlfriend
to my party.

184
00:08:47,151 --> 00:08:47,985
‎你准备好了吗？
You ready?

185
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:49,612
‎我还在留恋杰伊
I'm not over Jay.

186
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:53,032
‎-我的天 不会吧
‎-啥？
-Oh my God. No way.
-What?

187
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:56,244
‎就是说啊
[chuckles] I know!

188
00:08:56,327 --> 00:08:57,787
‎我也很惊讶
I'm surprised too.

189
00:08:58,496 --> 00:08:59,747
‎这都是我的错
And it's all my fault.

190
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:01,415
‎因为…我根本就是布兰达
Because, guys…

191
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:03,417
‎因为…我根本就是布兰达
-I'm Brenda.
-Brenda?

192
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:06,254
‎-布兰达？
‎-《飞越比佛利》里的布兰达
-Brenda Walsh, from <i>90210.</i>
-[Ozzie sighs]

193
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:09,674
‎布兰达对那个男人很执着
‎但她从来不去追那个男人
Brenda obsesses over the guy,
but she never <i>goes </i>for the guy.

194
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:13,553
[pop rock theme music playing]

195
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:14,512
[percussion plays]

196
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:24,397
‎（飞越点域镇）

197
00:09:25,106 --> 00:09:27,400
‎（莉亚）

198
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:30,319
‎（格温）

199
00:09:31,779 --> 00:09:34,115
‎（杰伊）

200
00:09:34,824 --> 00:09:37,285
‎（奥兹）

201
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,538
‎（内特）

202
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,624
‎（妮基）

203
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:46,335
‎（雷德）

204
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:48,921
‎（凯蒂）

205
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:52,675
‎（布莱恩奥斯丁饰大卫）

206
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,015
[class bell ringing]

207
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:05,187
‎人们总是说我在逃跑
All my life, people told me
I was running away.

208
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,272
‎但其实
But, really,

209
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:08,774
‎我一直在奔向一个人
I've been running <i>to</i> something.

210
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,067
‎是我 对吧？
It's me, isn't it?

211
00:10:10,776 --> 00:10:11,611
‎是的
It is.

212
00:10:19,827 --> 00:10:23,748
‎嘿 莉亚 今晚我要给派对做DJ
‎你想来吗？肯定超赞的
Hey, Leia. I'm DJing a party tonight.
You wanna come? It's gonna be fresh.

213
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:25,791
‎现在不行 大卫
Not now, David.

214
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,919
‎就因为我高一 是吗？
It's because I'm a freshman, isn't it?

215
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:32,548
[pop rock theme music plays]

216
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:36,844
‎也就是说
‎布兰达是一个被动戏多的受气包
So Brenda's the passive,
overly dramatic doormat.

217
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:38,512
‎这就说得通了
This makes sense now.

218
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:40,097
‎就是说吧？
[gasps and laughs] I know, right?

219
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:42,099
‎但你知道谁总能把帅哥追到手吗？
But you know who always gets the guy?

220
00:10:42,183 --> 00:10:45,436
‎娇贵人气金发女凯莉
Kelly, the popular blonde
with the rich-girl attitude.

221
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:48,522
[pop rock theme music playing]

222
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:49,440
[percussion plays]

223
00:10:50,983 --> 00:10:53,653
‎（飞越点域镇）

224
00:10:55,029 --> 00:10:57,031
[upbeat rock music playing]

225
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:01,994
‎人们总是说我在逃跑
All my life, people told me
I was running away.

226
00:11:02,578 --> 00:11:03,496
‎但其实
But, really,

227
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:05,665
‎我一直在奔向一个人
I've been running <i>to</i> something.

228
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:06,957
‎是我 对吧？
It's me, isn't it?

229
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,042
‎才怪 贱人 是我
No, bitch. It's me.

230
00:11:10,795 --> 00:11:12,588
‎-莉亚？
‎-是凯莉
-Leia?
-It's Kelly.

231
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:16,550
‎伙计们 今晚我要给派对做DJ
‎你们想来吗？肯定超赞的
Hey, guys. I'm DJing a party tonight.
You wanna come? It's gonna be fresh.

232
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:18,010
‎现在不行 大卫
Not now, David.

233
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:22,014
‎就因为我高一 是吗？
It's because I'm a freshman, isn't it?

234
00:11:22,098 --> 00:11:24,975
[pop rock theme plays, fades out]

235
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:28,562
‎我喜欢 介意我发挥一下下吗？
I like it.
Mind if I riff on it a little bit?

236
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:33,150
[pop rock theme music playing]

237
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:34,110
[percussion plays]

238
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:36,153
‎（飞越点域镇）

239
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:39,448
‎伙计们 今晚我要给派对做DJ
‎肯定超赞的
Hey, guys. I'm DJing a party.
It's gonna be fresh.

240
00:11:39,532 --> 00:11:42,576
‎有个超赞的霹雳舞者会来 瞅瞅
This totally rad breakdancer's
gonna be there. Check it.

241
00:11:43,953 --> 00:11:45,162
‎音乐走起
Drop that beat.

242
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:47,707
[old school hip-hop beat playing]

243
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:50,292
[students exclaiming]

244
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:02,304
‎我从没见过这么酷的娃
That's the coolest kid I've ever seen!

245
00:12:03,305 --> 00:12:05,975
[pop rock theme music plays, fades out]

246
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:08,686
‎不会吧 哥们儿？
Really, dude?

247
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:10,563
‎大卫从不骗人
David don't lie.

248
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,734
‎等杰伊和赛琳娜来参加派对
‎我就用凯莉的方式
When Jay and Serena show up at my party,
I'm gonna show 'em what's what.

249
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:16,235
‎让他们搞搞清楚状况
Kelly-style.

250
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:18,821
‎难怪我们跟男人同工不同酬
This is why we get paid 30% less than men.

251
00:12:20,781 --> 00:12:22,616
‎你不是对杰伊没执念了吗？
What happened to not obsessing over Jay?

252
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,201
‎我没有执念
I'm not obsessing.

253
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:26,704
‎我只是改变外表、行为和想法
‎让他回心转意
I'm just gonna change how I look
and how I act and how I think

254
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:27,621
‎我只是改变外表、行为和想法
‎让他回心转意
to win him back.

255
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:32,376
‎-喂！你这是干嘛？
‎-让你振作起来
-Hey! What was that for?
-To snap you out of it.

256
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,419
‎干嘛呀！
Dude!

257
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:35,045
‎嘿！
Hey!

258
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:36,380
‎好了 住手
Ow. Stop.

259
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,549
‎我是对这种剧情不感兴趣
I am the wrong audience for this.

260
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:39,717
‎别闹了！
[Leia] Ow!

261
00:12:40,259 --> 00:12:41,802
‎我准备好礼物了
-I got the gift.
-[Kitty gasps]

262
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,429
‎鲍勃去哪儿了？
-Where's Bob?
-Oh.

263
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:44,805
‎他嘛…
Well…

264
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:47,266
‎他搞得我抓狂 于是…
He was driving me crazy, so I…

265
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:50,060
‎我把感冒药掺在他的冰茶里了
I put some cold medicine in his iced tea.

266
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:53,731
‎还有他的土豆沙拉里
And some in his potato salad.

267
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:56,817
‎还有他的布丁里
Some more in his pudding.

268
00:12:58,068 --> 00:13:01,864
‎雷德 他…就是不肯消停
‎感觉就像…给犀牛下药
He just… He wouldn't go down, Red.
It was like… drugging a rhino.

269
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:06,076
‎反正哩 他在楼上睡得正香
Anyhoo, he's fast asleep upstairs.

270
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,455
‎你就等着看我给莉亚准备的礼物吧
Wait till you see what I got Leia.

271
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:14,043
‎鲍勃砸钱 我用心
Bob went expensive, but I went thoughtful.

272
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:16,295
‎你可真是贴心呢
You sweet, sweet man.

273
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:19,381
‎她专属的无绳电钻
Her own cordless drill.

274
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:25,012
‎你可真是笨呢
You stupid, stupid man.

275
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:29,141
‎多好的礼物啊 帮她自立
But it's a great gift.
It gives her independence.

276
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:33,145
‎她可以自己修东西 自己照顾自己
She can fix things on her own.
Take care of herself.

277
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,066
‎你干嘛那样看着我？
Why are you looking at me like that?

278
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:40,110
‎莫非我没说这是无绳的？
Did I not say it was cordless?

279
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:45,366
‎雷德 你得用青少年的思维思考
Red, you need to think like a teenager.

280
00:13:45,449 --> 00:13:47,660
‎你十五岁时想要什么？
What did you want when you were 15?

281
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:49,495
‎小儿麻痹症疫苗
A vaccine for polio.

282
00:13:51,205 --> 00:13:53,165
‎好吧 我继续找
All right. I'll keep looking.

283
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,418
‎乖乖…我肯定是累坏了
Man… I must have been really tired.

284
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:00,381
‎我在厅里睡着了
I fell asleep in the hallway.

285
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,969
‎嗯…倒时差可辛苦了
Well… you know,
that jet lag can be a killer.

286
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,097
‎我再给你拿点冰茶
Let me get you some more iced tea.

287
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:12,184
[rock music playing]

288
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:16,063
[Kitty] Ooh!

289
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:18,566
‎某人胃口不错呢
Somebody brought their appetite.

290
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:21,610
‎你最喜欢我哪道开胃菜？
So which one of my hors d'oeuvres
do you like best?

291
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,238
‎这个蛤蜊蘸酱…我超爱
This clam dip? Love!

292
00:14:26,824 --> 00:14:27,825
‎哎呀呀
Whoopsie.

293
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:34,373
‎好了 我习惯高跟鞋了 你可以放手了
Okay, I've figured out high heels.
You can let go now.

294
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:36,250
‎你要站在这里等杰伊吗？
So you're gonna stand here
and wait for Jay?

295
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,753
‎对呀 等他来了
‎我要像凯莉一样把他的脸啃烂
Yeah. And when he gets here,
I'm gonna grab him and Kelly his face off.

296
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:42,631
‎（一小时后）
[dramatic rock guitar riff plays]

297
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:46,760
‎太丢脸了
This is so embarrassing.

298
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:52,850
‎我以为我能让杰伊回心转意
‎但他根本不在乎 来都没有来
I thought I could win back Jay,
but he didn't even care enough to show.

299
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:54,643
‎我懂
I get it.

300
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:57,646
‎没人来“核桃咖啡馆”看我当DJ
No one came to watch me
DJ at the Peach Pit.

301
00:14:58,147 --> 00:14:59,690
‎连唐娜马丁都没来
Not even Donna Martin.

302
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:00,649
‎太糟糕了
It's the worst.

303
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:03,694
‎她在场下人怎么样？
What was she like? I mean, between scenes?

304
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:05,905
‎什么叫“场”？
What do you mean, "scenes"?

305
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:08,741
‎算了
Never mind.

306
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,411
‎谢谢你来参加我的生日派对 大卫
Thank you for coming
to my birthday, David.

307
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,872
‎-我最喜欢你了
‎-这个我爱听
-You were always my favorite.
-I'll take it.

308
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:20,419
‎你在跟谁说话？
Who are you talking to?

309
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:21,837
‎大卫 没谁
Uh, David. Nobody.

310
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:24,381
‎这样太傻了
This is stupid.

311
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:26,383
‎因为惦记杰伊 我整个生日都浪费了
I wasted my whole birthday
thinking about Jay,

312
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,968
‎而他显然已经向前看了
and he's clearly moved on.

313
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,178
‎我才不要继续可怜下去
I'm done being pathetic.

314
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:30,179
‎终于开窍了
Finally!

315
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,681
‎让开 他来了！
-[doorbell chimes]
-Move, he's here! Move, he's here!

316
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:35,684
‎鲍勃姥爷？
Grandpa Bob?

317
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:38,604
‎你是说汤姆琼斯姥爷
You mean Grandpa Tom Jones.

318
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:42,816
‎我来用你的生日礼物给你唱生日歌
I'm here to sing your birthday song
on your birthday gift.

319
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,653
‎你唱歌？当着我朋友？穿那件衣服？
You're gonna sing?
In front of my friends? In that jacket?

320
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:46,862
‎我要站那边去了
I'll be over here.

321
00:15:48,572 --> 00:15:49,740
‎汤姆琼斯？
Tom Jones?

322
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:54,119
‎更像是汤姆从沙发起身穷哼唧
‎你说是不是？
More like Tom groans
getting up from the couch. Am I right?

323
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:56,830
‎就是
I am right.

324
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:58,832
[soft karaoke instrumental playing]

325
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:01,961
‎歌放错了 但演出还要继续
Wrong song, but, hey, the show must go on.

326
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:06,799
‎我想把这首歌
‎献给我美丽的外孙女莉亚
I'd like to dedicate this song
to my beautiful granddaughter, Leia.

327
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:08,175
‎这首歌唱给你听
This one's for you.

328
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:09,426
‎坏了
Oh no.

329
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:12,221
<i>♪ Close your eyes ♪</i>

330
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:13,973
<i>♪ Make a wish ♪</i>

331
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:19,144
<i>♪ And blow out the candlelight ♪</i>

332
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,313
‎能行呢 这是首生日歌
Hey, it worked out. It's a birthday song.

333
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:23,273
‎这首不是生日歌
This is not a birthday song.

334
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:24,900
‎我们一起挺过去
We'll ride it out together.

335
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,569
<i>♪ I'll make love to you ♪</i>

336
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,488
<i>♪ Like you want me to ♪</i>

337
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:32,324
<i>♪ And I'll hold you tight ♪</i>

338
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:35,411
<i>♪ Baby, all through the night… ♪</i>

339
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,079
‎这是我们的歌
This is our song. [chuckles]

340
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,497
[Bob continues singing]

341
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:41,417
‎你第一次让我摸你屁股时
‎电台就在放这首歌
It was playing on the radio the first time
you let me touch your butt.

342
00:16:42,459 --> 00:16:43,961
‎你还记得
Oh, you remembered!

343
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:49,258
♪ <i>And I will not let go</i>
<i>Till you tell me to ♪</i>

344
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,509
‎想出去透透气吗？
Wanna get some air?

345
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,469
‎必须的
Oh God, yes.

346
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:56,223
<i>♪ Girl, relax ♪</i>

347
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:58,183
‎鲍勃 没人放松的了
Bob. Nobody's relaxed.

348
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:03,355
‎孩儿啊 你今天晚上好像不太好过啊
Seems like you might have had
a rough night, kiddo.

349
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:07,067
‎今天是我十五岁的第一天
‎可我一点也不开心
I've only been 15 for a day,
and so far I don't like it.

350
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,861
‎没有一件事顺心
I mean, nothing's gone right.

351
00:17:08,944 --> 00:17:10,738
‎感觉我都不知道自己在做什么
It's like I don't know what I'm doing.

352
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:11,822
‎怎么说呢
Well,

353
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:15,075
‎事事不可能总会顺心
everything's not gonna go right.

354
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:17,911
‎别这么为难自己
‎毕竟你有一半笨蛋血统
Give yourself a break.
You're half dumbass.

355
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,207
‎只是…
It's just…

356
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:26,295
‎其他人好像都活得明明白白
‎而我只能随机应变
Everyone else seems to have it all
figured out and I'm just making it all up.

357
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,631
‎娃啊 那我有坏消息要告诉你
Well, I hate to break it to you, kid,

358
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:34,303
‎大家都是一路随机应变
but we're all just making it up
as we go along.

359
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:37,056
‎所以 别太为难自己
So don't be so hard on yourself.

360
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,141
‎谢谢你 爷爷
Thanks, Grandpa.

361
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:42,394
‎嘿 等等
Oh. Hey, wait.

362
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:44,271
‎你不想要你的礼物吗？
Don't you want your present?

363
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,858
["Slow Ride" opening riff playing]

364
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:50,569
<i>♪ Slow ride… ♪</i>

365
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,948
‎车？你给我买了辆车？
A car? You got me a car?

366
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:56,784
‎它原来是你爸爸的
It belonged to your father.

367
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:01,288
‎明天我们帮你申请学员执照
‎我会教你怎么开车 好吧？
Tomorrow, we'll get your learner's permit,
and I'll teach you how to drive. Okay?

368
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:03,290
‎谢谢你 爷爷
Thank you, Grandpa.

369
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:05,250
‎这是我收到过最棒的礼物
This is the best present I've ever gotten.

370
00:18:05,334 --> 00:18:06,418
Oh…

371
00:18:07,002 --> 00:18:09,046
‎记得把这话告诉你鲍勃姥爷
Be sure to say that to Grandpa Bob.

372
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,257
‎孩儿啊 生日快乐
Happy birthday, kiddo.

373
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:15,177
<i>-♪ Slow ridin' woman, you're so fine ♪</i>
-[song fades out]

374
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,679
‎你把那辆“远景巡洋舰”送她了？
You gave her the Vista Cruiser?

375
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:21,809
‎乖乖 你净掐我命根子
Man, you really creamed my jeans.

376
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:28,190
‎你认输都不能正常点儿？
Can't you even lose like a normal person?

377
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:31,652
‎好了 雷德 这又不是比赛
Now, Red, it wasn't a competition.

378
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:37,282
‎我想为莉亚尽一份心
I wanted to do something nice for Leia.

379
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:40,953
‎你们真有福分 能跟她长久相处
You guys are lucky
to spend all this time with her.

380
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:45,666
‎我只希望她别忘了自己的鲍勃姥爷
I don't want her
to forget about her ol' Grandpa Bob.

381
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:46,834
Oh.

382
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:48,585
‎该死
Damn it.

383
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,296
‎鲍勃 你是个好人
You're a good man, Bob.

384
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:55,092
‎烦得要死 但是个好人
Annoying as hell, but a good man.

385
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,886
‎身边有你 是莉亚的福分
Leia is lucky to have you.

386
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:00,597
‎你们都把我整哭了
You guys are makin' me emotional.

387
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:04,059
‎我从来不哭的
And I never cry.

388
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,813
‎鲍勃 这里随时欢迎你来
Bob, you are welcome here anytime.

389
00:19:07,896 --> 00:19:09,106
[chuckles]

390
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,190
Ooh.

391
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:12,484
‎我得去方便方便
I gotta see a man about a clam. [chuckles]

392
00:19:15,779 --> 00:19:17,030
‎“随时”？
"Anytime"?

393
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,241
‎雷德 大家都是一家人
Red, he's family.

394
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:20,701
‎艾瑞克！
[grumbles] Eric!

395
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:26,248
[rapping on window]

396
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:29,293
‎杰伊？
Jay?

397
00:19:31,503 --> 00:19:33,255
‎喂 介意我进来吗？
Hey. Mind if I come in?

398
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:34,965
‎好吧 但派对结束了
Okay, but the party's over.

399
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:38,844
‎我知道 抱歉我错过了
[strains] Yeah. I'm sorry I missed it.

400
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:41,638
‎我只是觉得和赛琳娜一起来不太好
It just didn't feel right
to show up with Serena.

401
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:43,640
‎我还是不明白 我干嘛要邀请她
I still don't know why I invited her.

402
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,685
‎-我只是希望你能来
‎-我也想来
-I just wanted you to be there.
-I wanted to be there too.

403
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:50,397
‎不过…至少我可以祝你生日快乐
But… at least I can wish you
a happy birthday.

404
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:53,192
‎知道吗？不然就来不及了
You know? Before it's too late.

405
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:00,741
‎你这是怎么了？
Whoa. Where did that come from?

406
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:02,868
‎大概是我随机应变吧
I guess I'm just
making it up as I go along.

407
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:09,833
‎-你得跟赛琳娜分手
‎-赛琳娜是谁？
-You need to break up with Serena.
-Serena who?

408
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:10,876
[Jay chuckles]

409
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:13,253
["The World I Know"
by Collective Soul playing]

410
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,215
‎你想去开车兜风吗？
Hey, you wanna go for a drive?

411
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:18,091
‎-想啊 但我没有车
‎-这不成问题
Yeah, but I don't have a car.

412
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:19,551
‎-想啊 但我没有车
‎-这不成问题
[laughs softly] Not a problem.

413
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:25,933
<i>♪ So I walk up on high… ♪</i>

414
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:28,143
‎-嘿 我们接吻了
‎-我知道
-Hey, we kissed.
-I know.

415
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:30,437
‎今年生日最棒了
This is the best birthday.

416
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:33,941
[siren wails]

417
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:37,152
‎酷一点
Just be cool.

418
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:39,238
‎可我这辈子没酷过 怎么办？
You mean, for the first time in my life?!

419
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:41,490
<i>♪ While the tears roll down ♪</i>

420
00:20:42,115 --> 00:20:44,660
<i>♪ 'Cause it's the world I know ♪</i>

421
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,746
<i>♪ Oh, it's the world I know ♪</i>

422
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,750
[rock music playing]

423
00:21:25,158 --> 00:21:28,787
‎字幕翻译：Zeo Niu

